cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on developing an autonomous visual assistant for robot operations, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also extensively uses computer vision techniques to enable the visual assistant to navigate through unstructured or confined spaces, which makes cs.CV a likely sub-category. The use of risk-aware motion planning and autonomy in the visual assistant also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential applications of the proposed system in domains such as disaster robots and bomb squads, which fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential benefits of reducing manpower and teamwork demand, which suggests the involvement of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) techniques.
